Welcome to [Your System Name] (“the System”), an electronic health record (EHR) and clinic management platform designed for primary care clinics. By accessing or using this System, you (“User,” “Doctor,” “Staff,” or “Clinic Administrator”) agree to comply with and be bound by the following Terms and Conditions. Please read them carefully before using the System.

1. Acceptance of Terms

By registering, accessing, or using the System, you agree to these Terms and Conditions and our Privacy Policy. If you do not agree with any part of these terms, you must not use the System.

2. System Description

The [Your System Name] provides tools for:

Managing patient records and medical histories,

Allowing authorized healthcare professionals to upload, update, and access patient data,

Tracking patient visits, prescriptions, and diagnostic results,

Supporting primary care clinic operations such as billing, appointments, and reporting.

This System is intended solely for authorized healthcare use and not for public access.

3. Authorized Users

Only registered and authorized personnel — including doctors, nurses, medical technologists, and administrative staff — are allowed to access or upload patient information.
Users must:

Maintain confidentiality of login credentials,

Use the System strictly for legitimate healthcare and administrative purposes,

Immediately report any unauthorized access or suspected security breach.

Unauthorized access or misuse may result in suspension or termination of access privileges and possible legal action.

4. Data Ownership and Privacy

All patient data stored in the System remains the property of the Clinic or Healthcare Provider and the patient to whom the data pertains.

The System acts as a secure platform for data management and does not claim ownership of uploaded medical records.

Users must comply with the Data Privacy Act of 2012 (Republic Act No. 10173) and all applicable data protection laws.

Any uploading, viewing, or sharing of patient data must be done only with authorized consent and in accordance with legal and ethical guidelines.

5. Responsibilities of Users

Users agree to:

Enter only accurate and truthful information,

Avoid uploading harmful or malicious files,

Use the System in a manner that does not disrupt operations or compromise data integrity,

Respect patient confidentiality at all times.

Any violation may lead to disciplinary and/or legal consequences.

6. System Availability and Maintenance

The System may be subject to:

Routine maintenance or updates,

Temporary unavailability due to technical issues or system upgrades.

We will make reasonable efforts to notify users of planned downtime. The developers or administrators are not liable for any loss of data or service interruptions beyond reasonable control.

7. Security

We implement administrative, technical, and physical safeguards to protect patient information.
However, no electronic system is completely secure. Users are responsible for:

Using strong passwords,

Logging out after each session,

Protecting their account credentials.

8. Limitation of Liability

The System and its administrators shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental, or consequential damages arising from:

Misuse of the platform,

Loss of data due to user negligence,

Unauthorized access by third parties,

Errors or omissions in uploaded patient information.

Users acknowledge that the accuracy and integrity of patient records depend on the data they provide.

9. Modification of Terms

We reserve the right to modify or update these Terms at any time. Continued use of the System after updates constitutes acceptance of the revised Terms.

10. Termination of Access

We may suspend or terminate user accounts if:

The user violates these Terms,

There is evidence of unauthorized access or misuse,

The clinic or organization requests account removal.

All data associated with terminated accounts will be handled in accordance with our data retention and privacy policy.

11. Governing Law

These Terms are governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the Republic of the Philippines.
Any disputes arising from the use of this System shall be resolved through amicable settlement or, if necessary, before the proper courts of Cebu City, Philippines.

12. Contact Information

For questions, feedback, or legal concerns about these Terms, please contact:
[Clinic or Developer Name]
Email: [insert email address]
Phone: [insert contact number]
Address: [insert address]
